30/05/2004
TIRANA, Albania - Central Electoral Commission Chairman Ilirjan Celibashi met on Thursday (27 May) with the mayors of the largest towns, urging them to verify voter lists for the next general elections, scheduled for July 2005. 
Celibashi asked the mayors to work to guarantee accurate voter registration, strengthening the transparency of the election process.
In other news, US Assistant Secretary of Commerce William H. 
Lash visited Tirana on Friday and said Washington wants to make economic relations with Albania as strong as their political relations. 
A team of US experts will arrive shortly to help develop small and medium-sized businesses, as well as assist in the fight against corruption. 
(Albanian news - 29/05/04)
